This paper deals with scene evolution prediction for automated driving, which involves computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO) techniques. The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) sub-categories. Finally, the application of the proposed method to autonomous driving systems falls under the systems and control (SY) sub-category.
